# Rory the Marketer — Cursor Rules

## Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router, no src/ dir)
- TypeScript strict
- Tailwind CSS v4
- Anthropic SDK for Claude API calls

## File conventions
- `app/` — pages and API routes (Next.js App Router)
- `lib/` — shared server utilities (brands, context bundle, context library storage)
- `context/` — brand context markdown files (voice, personas, USPs, etc.)
- `data/{brandId}/` — per-brand synced/generated data (JSON)
- `docs/` — implementation docs

## Patterns
- Brand-aware: most API routes accept `brand` param; use `getBrand()` to validate
- Context bundle: `getContextBundle(brandId)` reads markdown files from `context/`
- Context library: CRUD via `lib/context-library-storage.ts`; if `DATABASE_URL` is set, Postgres (Prisma); else `data/{brandId}/context-library.json`
- API routes return JSON; use `NextResponse.json()`
- Claude calls use `@anthropic-ai/sdk` with context injected into system prompts

## Style
- Light, clean UI (not dark theme)
- Tailwind utility classes, no component library
- CSS variables defined in `app/globals.css` (accent, muted, border, surface, etc.)
- Keep components simple and focused

## Important
- All context files are markdown in `context/` — read at runtime, not bundled
- Brand ID for Wine Spies is "winespies"
- Don't hardcode API keys; use env vars
- Server-side only: fs operations, API keys, Claude calls
